al details born october   greenville washington county mississippi usa died january   aged  monroe louisiana resting place delhi masonic cemetery in delhi in richland parish political party republican candidate for louisiana state senate  louisiana elections commissioner  member franklin parish board of elections spouses  melba jo thomas divorced  divorced  linda rae martin baker surviving widow children john henry baker iv deceased jefferi b ryals two granddaughters one deceased parents cecelia myers baker radau mother residence delhi louisiana land holdings in franklin parish occupation farmer businessman john henry baker iii october   – january   was a farmer and landowner from franklin parish in northeastern louisiana who was active in the rebirth of the republican party in his state during the s and s baker was his partys nominee for the district  seat in the louisiana state senate in  and for the former position of state elections commissioner in  he was the first to propose the abolition of the commissioners post originally called the custodian of voting machines with the return of the duties to the secretary of state bakers proposal was adopted a quarter of a century later in  contents  background education farming  franklin parish police jury  running for the state senate  running for constitutional convention delegate  challenging jerry fowler  abolish the office  later years  references background education farmingedit baker was born in greenville in washington county in western mississippi to john henry baker jr and cecilia myers baker radau  a native of rockdale in milam county texas whose second husband was fred c radau  he was reared in a rural area near delhi located in neighboring richland parish but the baker ancestral property and his voting residence was in northern franklin parish bakers brother bob roy baker  of delhi died a month after the passing of bakers son john henry hank baker iv  as a teenager john henry and bob roy baker left the area to attend marion military institute in marion alabama baker thereafter served in the united states air force from  to  after his military duties ended baker returned to farming he was a methodist baker was twice divorced he was married until his death to his third wife the former linda rae martin his surviving widow from his first marriage to the former melba jo thomas born  was born john hank baker iv who is interred at myrtle memorial cemetery in winnsboro baker was survived by a daughter jefferi baker ryals born october  and her husband robert lee ryals born march  of delhi in  baker established kpch  fm radio outlet the peach station in ruston in  he sold the company which offers s and s oldies music franklin parish police juryedit in  baker at thirtythree was elected as a democrat to the franklin parish police jury equivalent of county commission in otherm states he won his primary then equivalent to election by only nineteen votes in february  he switched to the republican party and set forth to build a competitive twoparty system in his region and state a goal for which there was no political infrastructure while he was on the police jury the body joined the parish north delta economic planning and development council baker served on this council during his single term on the jury while on the jury baker was appointed to the franklin parish library board on which he served for thirteen years baker was also a chairman of the franklin parish republican party intermittently since the s running for the state senateedit in the winter of  to  baker ran for the state senate against the yearold democratic nominee james h jim brown a graduate of tulane university in new orleans brown at the time was a politically ambitious lawyer in ferriday in concordia parish located along the mississippi river across from natchez mississippi besides franklin and concordia the district included catahoula jonesville and tensas st joseph and newellton parishes the outgoing senator was j c sonny gilbert of sicily island in catahoula parish gilbert ran successfully for the state house that year after he left the legislature he switched to republican affiliation brown was an easy winner in the general election  votes  percent to bakers   percent baker had been the first republican ever to contest the nd district seat with the boundaries altered the district for the first time elected a republican state senator on november   when gop businessman neil riser of columbia the seat of caldwell parish defeated the democratic candidate bryant hammett of ferriday the senate seat was vacated by the termlimited democrat noble ellington of winnsboro who instead returned to the louisiana house after an absence of twelve years running for constitutional convention delegateedit in august  five months after he lost the state senate race baker ran unsuccessfully in the nonpartisan race for delegate to the state constitutional convention the convention was held in baton rouge in  it adopted a new constitution which voters approved in a special election held in the spring of  baker filed for delegate in the state legislative district for franklin and tensas parishes he was defeated by democratic state representative lantz womack of winnsboro as a young man womack had played baseball for the former winnsboro red sox at a time when many small towns had their own teams bakers father organized two winnsboro teams one for whites and the other for africanamerican players womack a businessman and farmer was first elected to the house seat from franklin parish in a special election in  and he held the seat until  in his last reelection on february   womack polled  percent of the vote against the republican nominee terry clingan – a barber from mangham in richland parish and later from baskin a village in franklin parish coincidentally womack was once a bookkeeper for the bakers challenging jerry fowleredit in  baker announced that he would challenge the democrat jerry fowler then a natchitoches businessman in the race for elections commissioner fowler born  was seeking to succeed his ailing father douglas fowler the former red river parish clerk of court and onetime coushatta mayor fowler had been appointed to the post by the late governor earl kemp long after long had quarreled with secretary of state wade o martin jr by procuring legislative consent to remove the elections office from the domain of the secretary of state douglas fowler was then elected to his first full term in  and then reelected with minimal opposition in    and  the primaries for the three latter elections were actually held late in   and  to louisiana voters the name fowler became synonymous with the management of elections – the two won a total of ten consecutive elections abolish the officeedit baker ran for elections commissioner basing his campaign on abolishing the useless office which then had a salary of  per year and returning its duties to the secretary of state where they had been before earl long punished martin who had continued to be reelected secretary of state until his retirement in  ironically what baker was proposing would have worked to the advantage of bakers former rival state senator jim brown who would be elected secretary of state in the same  election when baker offered his proposal to abolish the very office for which he was seeking election he began to make headway he won a student mock poll at louisiana state university at alexandria and several other colleges as well as the endorsements of good government groups and most of the states newspapers the new orleans timespicayune did not endorse baker however but recommended his idea of abolishing the office baker polled  votes in the nonpartisan blanket primary just enough to enter the  general election against jerry fowler who had been a former professional football player and a former educator baker and republican gubernatorial candidate david c treen then of jefferson parish were the first louisiana republicans to win statewide general election slots since the implementation of the jungle primary law in  the law did not take effect for congressional elections until  and it ended for those elections in  but was reinstated in  in the second round of balloting fowler polled  votes  percent to bakers   percent baker won  percent in his own franklin parish which treen lost to the democrat louis lambert of baton rouge baker won  percent and  percent in his neighboring richland and ouachita parishes respectively he polled  percent in caddo parish shreveport and ran nearly as well in calcasieu parish lake charles where he had the support of former state senator robert g bob jones the stockbroker son of former governor sam houston jones like his father jerry fowler was also elected commissioner five times     and  in  however he finished in third place in the primary after bribery allegations surfaced he would later serve a prison sentence the post was then won by the only republican who ever held it suzanne haik terrell in  more than four decades after longs death the elections division was hence returned to its original administrative home it was left to commissioner terrell to implement bakers longstanding proposal baker never received political credit for his good government proposal from  later yearsedit in  governor treen appointed baker to the louisiana athletic commission since renamed the louisiana state boxing and wrestling commission that same year baker was a delegate to the republican national convention in detroit michigan which first nominated the ronald w reagan and george h w bush ticket as of  baker was still a member of the franklin parish board of election supervisors by virtue of his being the parish republican chairman baker died at the age of eighty early in  at st francis hospital in monroe he is interred at delhi masonic cemetery in delhi biography portal mississippi portal louisiana portal politics portal agriculture portal united states air force portal methodism portal referencesedit  cecelia celia myers radau findagravecom retrieved may     a b bob roy baker findagravecom retrieved may     john henry hank baker iv findagravecom retrieved may     a b john henry baker iii findagravecom retrieved may     kpch radio radiotimecom retrieved january     election returns voterportalsoslagov november   retrieved may     membership of the louisiana house of representatives  pdf houselouisianagov archived from the original pdf on october   retrieved may     shreveport journal october   p d  the alexandria daily town talk november   p d  baton rouge statetimes december   p c  jerry m fowler the baton rouge advocate january   retrieved may     alan ehrenhalt august   the most ridiculous elective office in the history of state government is about to pass out of existence jewish world review retrieved may    retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlejohnhenrybakeroldid categories  births deathspoliticians from greenville mississippimarion military institute alumnipeople from franklin parish louisianapeople from delhi louisianafarmers from louisianaparish jurors and commissioners in louisianalouisiana democratslouisiana republicansamerican united methodistshidden categories pages using infobox officeholder with an atypical party valuepages using infobox officeholder with unknown parameters navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version languages add links this page was last edited on  april  at  text is available under the creative commons 